text=(:notitle:)%0a(:table valign=top:)%0a(:cellnr colspan=3 width=380 bgcolor=#74483f align=center:)%0a!!%25white%25Bad Moon Rising%25white%25%0a(:cellnr rowspan=30 width=400 align=center:) http://images4.wikia.nocookie.net/__cb20090502015761/whitewolf/images/5/5e/SkullWTF.png%0a(:cellnr width=340 colspan=2 align=center:)%0ahttp://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/wtf/headers/wtf_s.png%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Totem:'''%0a(:cell width=190:) Old Creeper%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Membership:'''%0a(:cell width=190:) 3%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Alpha:'''%0a(:cell width=190:) The leadership of this pack shifts with the phases of the moon.%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Territory:''' %0a(:cell width=190:) Savannah National Wildlife Refuge%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Position:'''%0a(:cell width=190:) Ritualists%0a%0a%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Player:''' %0a(:cell width=190:) NPC: LeeK%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Theme Music:''' %0a(:cell width=190:) [[http://www.youtube.com/ |Music]]%0a(:tableend:)%0a%25%25http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/wtf/headers/wtf_d.png%0a%0aBad Moon Rising is one of the newer packs in Savannah, Georgia. They are staunch supporters of the tenets of the Oath and live a seclusive existence in territory that was granted to them by the Lords of Mourning Glory.%0a%0aThe pack hides their faces beneath masks crafted from the bones of animals that symbolize the Hunt or a connection to Luna. They have a deeper connection to the Hisil than other packs with two of their members coming from the Reynolds bloodline. They have become adept at the performance of uratha rituals and usually are the pack tasked with leading other Itheaur and ritualists in carrying them out.%0a%0aThey share leadership jointly between pack members, shifting who is the acting leader in accordance with the phases of the moon. Their obsession with the blessings of Luna have led to rumors that they have been infected by her madness.%0a%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%25%25http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/wtf/headers/wtf_h.png%0a%0aBad Moon Rising is a newer pack that was formed after the events of the Brethren War. They formed from one of the groups of First Changers that were discovered after the Hegemony took hold. They survived their Rites of Initiation and chose to stay together, forming a pack that submitted itself to the rule of the Hegemony in exchange for a lease of territory from the Alpha pack.%0a%0aThey are vassals of Lord Frostbite, owing fealty to his pack for the verdant territory he has offered. They are influential despite their lacking members and meager territory, but will form alliances with other smaller packs to influence Hegemony policy and build up their voice against those of larger packs like the Hellriders or the Dozen.%0a%0aThey have an extreme mistrust for the Skinner Wolf-Blooded Family and the pack of werewolves that lord over them.%0a%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%25%25http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/wtf/headers/wtf_rph.png%0a''The Moon's Love -'' Bad Moon Rising maintains a deeper connection to the lunes than other packs. This has brought rumors of derangement in their ranks, but they are knowledgeable in interpreting any omens or strange occult happenings a PC may encounter.%0a%0a''Ritualists -'' This pack is known for their knowledge of rituals. Those werewolves looking to increase their own knowledge of rites may seek them out for tutelage, but what price will they pay?%0a%0a''Testing Loyalties -'' The shifting allegiances of this pack are as fluid as the faces of the moon. How far can they be trusted? Their faces are constantly hidden beneath masks and they spend too much time in the Hisil. This pack might request strange favors of the PCs with no logical or discernible purpose.%0a%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%25%25http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/wtf/headers/wtf_q.png%0a"You should trust in our Mother. Her Light will show you the way." - Blood-Judgement, Blood Talon and Elodoth for Bad Moon Rising%0a%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a(:include CityBook.WerewolfNavigationBar:)
